Source.Contents:
/#
 The specification of how a calculation agent will be determined.
 #/
enum FpML5.confirmation.CalculationAgentPartyEnum {
    # The party that gives notice of exercise. Per 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 11.1. Parties, paragraph (d).
    ExercisingParty 
    # The party that is given notice of exercise. Per 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 11.1. Parties, paragraph (e).
    NonExercisingParty 
    # The Calculation Agent is determined by reference to the relevant master agreement.
    AsSpecifiedInMasterAgreement 
    # The Calculation Agent is determined by reference to the relevant standard terms supplement.
    AsSpecifiedInStandardTermsSupplement 
    # Both parties with joined rights to be a calculation agent.
    Both 

}

ExercisingParty.Doc: The party that gives notice of exercise. Per 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 11.1. Parties, paragraph (d).
ExercisingParty.Name: ExercisingParty

NonExercisingParty.Doc: The party that is given notice of exercise. Per 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 11.1. Parties, paragraph (e).
NonExercisingParty.Name: NonExercisingParty

AsSpecifiedInMasterAgreement.Doc: The Calculation Agent is determined by reference to the relevant master agreement.
AsSpecifiedInMasterAgreement.Name: AsSpecifiedInMasterAgreement

AsSpecifiedInStandardTermsSupplement.Doc: The Calculation Agent is determined by reference to the relevant standard terms supplement.
AsSpecifiedInStandardTermsSupplement.Name: AsSpecifiedInStandardTermsSupplement

Both.Doc: Both parties with joined rights to be a calculation agent.
Both.Name: Both
